This paper deals with natural language processing and the extraction of idiomatic expressions, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of automatic tools and machine learning algorithms, which are common in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the potential for extending the extraction method to other languages, which could fall under the sub-category of natural language engineering (cs.NE).
